BRIARDY v. KINGS COUNTY et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, Second Department February 11, 1895.) Appeal from special term, Kings county. Action by Owen Briardy against the county of Kings and the county of Queens for personal injuries. From a judgment dismissing the complaint, plaintiff appeals.

Argued before DYKMAN, PRATT, and CULLEN, JJ.

Grout, De Fere & Mayer, for appellant. George F. Elliott, for respondent Kings county. Frances H. Van Vechten, for respondent Queens county. PER CURIAM.

The judgment appealed from should be affirmed, with costs and disbursements, on opinion in Albrecht v. Queens Co., 32 N. Y. Supp. 473.
